# RentFlow Project Context

Project: RentFlow — Car Rental Booking System Rebuild.
Architecture: modular monolith REST API.
Stack: Java 21, Spring Boot, PostgreSQL, Redis, MinIO, Flyway, Docker Compose, Testcontainers.
Goal: production-style backend portfolio.

Core portfolio proof:
Idempotency-Key + PostgreSQL SELECT FOR UPDATE + Testcontainers concurrent booking test.

## Tech Stack

| Component | Technology |
|---|---|
| Language | Java 21 |
| Framework | Spring Boot |
| Database | PostgreSQL 16 |
| Migrations | Flyway |
| Cache/Session | Redis 7 |
| File Storage | MinIO / S3 |
| API Docs | SpringDoc OpenAPI |
| Testing | JUnit 5, Mockito, Testcontainers |
| Build | Maven |
| Container | Docker Compose |

## Package Structure

```
com.rentflow
├── auth          # Authentication: register, login, refresh, logout
├── user          # User profile, driver verification
├── vehicle       # Vehicle CRUD and state machine
├── listing       # Listing CRUD, submit, admin approval
├── availability  # Availability calendar, block/unblock
├── booking       # Booking creation, cancellation
├── payment       # Payment stub: authorize, capture, void, refund
├── common        # Shared: config, exception, security, pagination
├── audit         # Audit logging
├── notification  # User notifications
├── outbox        # Event outbox
├── file         # File metadata
├── trip         # Trip check-in/check-out
├── review       # Reviews
├── dispute      # Disputes
└── report       # Reports
```

## Always Follow

- docs/srs.md — Full requirements reference
- docs/roadmap.md — Implementation phases
- docs/p0-priorities.md — P0 feature checklist
- current docs/phase-*.md — Current phase plan

## Critical Rules

1. Never implement P1/P2 features before completing P0.
2. Never implement Kafka before outbox pattern works.
3. Never implement real payment gateway — use payment stub.
4. The concurrent booking test (10 requests, 1 success) is the portfolio proof.
5. All state-changing operations require Idempotency-Key.
6. SELECT FOR UPDATE order must be deterministic: always `ORDER BY available_date ASC`.
